.TH COMPROSE 1 "July 2026" "comprose 0.1.0"
.SH NAME
comprose \- Create and import prose content entries
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B comprose
\fIhelp\fR
.br
.B comprose
\fInew\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fB-s\fR \fISLUG\fR] [\fB-t\fR \fITITLE\fR]
.br
.B comprose
\fIimport\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIPATH\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B comprose
creates Markdown entry scaffolds for prose-oriented static sites.
It can also import a directory containing Markdown, optional CSS, and referenced images into a selected Mustache-backed template layout.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B help
Show the usage screen.
.TP
.B new
Create a new content entry scaffold.
.TP
.B import
Import a directory into a new content entry.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --template \fINAME-OR-PATH\fR
Set the template layout. Built-in templates are \fBastro-content\fR and \fBmiddleman-blog\fR. Defaults to \fBastro-content\fR.
.TP
.B \-s \fISLUG\fR
Set the entry slug.
.TP
.B \-t \fITITLE\fR
Set the entry title.
.TP
.B \-d \fIISO-8601\fR
Set the entry date. Date-only, date-time, and date-time with offset values are accepted.
.TP
.B \-k\fR, \fB--type\fR, \fB--kind\fR \fIKIND\fR
Set the entry kind. Valid values are \fIarticle\fR and \fInote\fR.
.TP
.B \-g \fITAG\fR
Add a tag to frontmatter. May be repeated.
.TP
.B \-i \fIPATH\fR
Copy an image into the entry asset directory. May be repeated.
.TP
.B \-e
Open created text files in \fBEDITOR\fR after scaffolding.
.TP
.B \-o
Open the public folder in Finder after scaffolding.
.TP
.B \-f
For \fBimport\fR, replace an existing generated entry.
.TP
.B \-c\fR, \fB--collection\fR \fINAME\fR
Set the content collection name. Defaults to the current directory name.
.TP
.B --pubname \fINAME\fR
Set the generated frontmatter \fBpubname\fR.
.SH TEMPLATES
.TP
.B astro-content
Writes \fBsrc/content/<collection>/<date>-<slug>/index.md\fR, a matching stylesheet, and assets under \fBpublic/<collection>/<slug>/\fR.
.TP
.B middleman-blog
Writes \fBsource/<collection>/<slug>.html.md\fR and assets under \fBsource/<collection>/<slug>/\fR. It does not create a stylesheet by default.
.PP
Template directories define output paths directly. Directory and file names can contain path variables such as \fB[collection]\fR, \fB[date]\fR, and \fB[slug]\fR. Files ending in \fB.mustache\fR are rendered and written without the suffix. A \fB.comprose-assets\fR marker file marks the directory where copied images are written.
.PP
Template names are resolved as built-in templates first, then as \fB.comprose/templates/<name>\fR in the current directory or a parent directory, then as \fB.config/comprose/templates/<name>\fR in the current directory or a parent directory, then as \fB$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/comprose/templates/<name>\fR or \fB$HOME/.config/comprose/templates/<name>\fR, then as a relative or absolute path passed to \fB--template\fR.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Create a new article:
.nf
.B comprose new --template astro-content -c journal --pubname example-journal -s my-new-entry
.fi
.TP
Create a Middleman-style entry:
.nf
.B comprose new --template middleman-blog -c posts -s my-new-entry
.fi
.TP
Import a prepared source directory:
.nf
.B comprose import --template middleman-blog -c posts /tmp/source-entry
.fi
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B Node.js
Used to run the command-line tool.
.TP
.B Mustache
Used to render entry and stylesheet templates.
.TP
.B sharp
Used to convert JPEG, WebP, and related image inputs to AVIF.
.TP
.B ImageMagick
Used for HEIC, PNG, and GIF import processing.
